# CP Air King — Closing

This is your sales team app, converted from a Claude artifact into a real, deployable
web app. Follow these steps in order — no coding required, just clicking through setup screens.

Total time: about 10–15 minutes.

---

## 1. Create your database (Supabase) — ~3 min

1. Go to https://supabase.com and sign up (free).
2. Click **New Project**. Pick any name and password (save the password somewhere).
3. Once it's created, go to the **SQL Editor** tab -> **New query**.
4. Open `supabase-schema.sql` (in this folder), copy all of it, paste it into the SQL editor, and click **Run**.
   This creates the one table the app needs.
5. Go to **Project Settings -> API**. You'll need two values from this page in step 3 below:
   - **Project URL**
   - **anon / public key**

## 2. Put the code on GitHub — ~3 min

1. Go to https://github.com and sign up if you don't have an account.
2. Click **New repository**. Name it something like `cpair-king-closing`. Keep it Private if you'd like. Click **Create repository**.
3. On the next page, click **uploading an existing file**.
4. Drag in every file and folder from this project (keep the folder structure — `src/` should stay a folder).
   Do **not** upload the `node_modules` folder if you have one (there shouldn't be one yet) or your `.env` file if you made one — `.gitignore` already excludes both, but double-check.
5. Click **Commit changes**.

## 3. Deploy it live (Vercel) — ~3 min

1. Go to https://vercel.com and sign up using your GitHub account (this makes step 2 automatic).
2. Click **Add New -> Project**, and select the `cpair-king-closing` repo you just created.
3. Before clicking Deploy, open **Environment Variables** and add:
   - `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` -> paste your Supabase Project URL from step 1
   - `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` -> paste your Supabase anon/public key from step 1
4. Click **Deploy**.
5. After a minute, you'll get a live URL like `cpair-king-closing.vercel.app` — that's your app, live on the web.

From now on, whenever you (or anyone) push new code changes to the GitHub repo, Vercel automatically redeploys the site.

## 4. Try it

Open your new URL. The first visit lets you set up your admin PIN. From there it works exactly
like it did as a Claude artifact — reps sign up with a name + PIN, everything is shared and saved
for the whole team.

## Optional: custom domain

In Vercel, go to your project -> **Settings -> Domains** and add a domain you own
(e.g. `app.cpair.com`). Vercel will show you a couple of DNS records to add at your domain
registrar — takes a few minutes to go live once added.

## A security note

Logins here are name + 4-digit PIN, not full encrypted-password accounts — the same
trade-off this app had as a Claude artifact. That's fine for a small, trusted internal
team, but don't let anyone reuse a real password as their PIN. If you outgrow this and
want real secure accounts later, that means adding Supabase Auth — worth a separate
follow-up build when you're ready.
